news.title: Home sales in USA rise 3.4% in October 2024
news.para: Existing home sales rose 3.4% last month, from September, to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 3.96 million, the National Association of Realtors said Thursday. That matches the annual pace set in July.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body identifies 1,500 illegal constructions across city
news.para: GHMC officials report that these violations primarily involve construction of extra floors, encroachments on govt or private land, road encroachments, deviations from approved plans, and construction without proper approvals.

news.title: Lucknow development body resolves 41 property related issues
news.para: Lucknow Development Authority received a total of 41 applications related to mutation, transfer and illegal construction during its ‘Pradhikaran Diwas' (authority day) held at the LDA building on Thursday.

news.title: Uttarakhand pollution control board fines 49 Mussoorie hotels for eco violations
news.para: These hotels were penalised earlier this year for similar violations. However, UPCB confirmed that fines paid previously will be deducted from the revised penalties. Dhakate said, "The NGT directed us to reassess the penalties for these hotels."

news.title: Lucknow: Construction sites flouting green norms worsens air pollution
news.para: As per NGT rules, construction materials like sand, bricks and cement must be covered to prevent dust, and measures like water sprinkling, dust barriers and proper waste disposal are mandatory.

news.title: Karnataka HC allows banks to sell mortgaged property in case of loan defaults
news.para: This decision was made whilst quashing an endorsement dated July 18, 2023, issued to South Canara District Central Cooperative Bank Ltd.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Land rates in Bodakdev may see six-fold increase
news.para: In 2011, the jantri rate for plots 368 and 380 in TP Scheme No. 50 in Bodakdev was Rs 10,700 per sq m. The proposed rate now ranges between Rs 58,000 and Rs 60,000 per sq m.

news.title: Nearly 80,000 lifts in Noida yet to register under new UP lift act
news.para: A govt order issued on Sept 25, directed district administrations under Meerut division, which includes Noida and Ghaziabad, to set up five-member committees that would investigate lift-related accidents and prepare reports on their maintenance, safety, and operation under the new Act.

news.title: Defence nod must for construction on old grant lands post-Secunderabad merger
news.para: The DGDE officer clarified that if municipal laws replace the Cantonment Act, 2006, in civil areas of cantonments, the building by-laws of the neighbouring municipality will apply to excised areas.

news.title: Nippon Life India acquires office space for Rs 486 crore in Mumbai
news.para: The asset management company is planning to shift its headquarters in this office spread over 52,162 sq ft from Peninsula Business Park in the vicinity.

news.title: Housing minister announces survey of homeless people in Ladakh
news.para: "A survey of all homeless people will be conducted in the Union Territory so that they can avail the benefits of PM Awas Yojana. The ministry will ensure that no person remains homeless in Ladakh," said Manohar Lal Khattar.

news.title: Average home prices in seven cities at Rs 1.23 crore in H1 FY25: Anarock
news.para: The data reveals that NCR saw the highest average ticket size growth – from approximately Rs 93 lakh in H1 FY24 to over Rs 1.45 crore in H1 FY25. While the value of sold inventory increased by 55% in this period, the total number of units sold declined by 1%.

news.title: Mall operators to see revenue growth of 10-12% in FY25: Report
news.para: High revenue growth last fiscal was driven by full-year contribution of malls launched towards the end of fiscal 2023, supplemented by the half year impact of those that were launched by mid last fiscal; on a like-to-like basis, revenue growth remained stable at ~5%.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh HC orders closure of HPTDC’s 18 loss making prime hotels
news.para: Justice Goel, therefore, directed closure of these 18 hotels in order to ensure that public resources are not wasted by the corporation in the upkeep of these “white elephants” as running of these properties is apparently not financially viable.

news.title: Equity investments in real estate sector to cross $10-11 billion in 2024: Report
news.para: Equity capital inflows touched $8.9 billion between January and September 2024, registering a 46% year-on-year growth.

news.title: Ambuja Cements' stocks dip 17.59%, ACC tanks 14.54% after Gautam Adani's US indictments
news.para: ​​ The stock of the group's flagship firm Adani Enterprises plunged 22.99 per cent, Adani Ports dived 20 per cent, Adani Energy Solutions tanked 20 per cent, Adani Green Energy plummeted 19.53 per cent and Adani Total Gas tumbled 18.14 per cent on the BSE.

news.title: Odisha government to bring in new rehab and resettlement policy for land losers
news.para: ‘Land for land' will be an option besides the existing cash for land compensation. The new policy will replace the 2006 policy.

news.title: Rajasthan government and centre to jointly operate Jaipur metro’s extended lines
news.para: Once the joint venture comes through, state govt will need to cover only 20% of the project's construction cost, said officials. While the Union govt will contribute an additional 20% to the project, the remaining 60% cost will be covered through a soft loan, they added.

news.title: Telangana HC orders land survey to resolve Patelguda villa demolition dispute
news.para: Telangana high court has directed the assistant director of survey and land records of Sangareddy district to survey the land situated at survey numbers 6 and 12 of Patelguda.

news.title: Hyderabad civic body demolishes five-storey building in Gachibowli
news.para: The building, constructed about two years ago, consists of four floors and a penthouse with 12 rooms, all crammed into a compact plot of just 50 square yards.
